## 2. Code Snippets — MIT License

Code samples embedded in the chapters and interview-prep files (anything inside a fenced
code block intended to be run — Dockerfiles, Terraform HCL, Python, YAML, Bash commands,
CI/CD configs, etc.) are additionally licensed under the MIT License, so they may be freely
reused, modified, and included in commercial projects. See LICENSE-CODE for the full text.

Where it is ambiguous whether something is "code" or "written content" (e.g. an annotated,
narrative code walkthrough), the CC BY-NC-SA 4.0 terms govern the surrounding prose and
explanation, while the runnable code itself remains MIT.
